From b2e3ba8ad0291788d77dfd0f44488033c3b29145 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yuvarani V <yuvarani@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Oct 2025 11:26:58 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL: Fix link ID leak during AP MLD link setup
 failure

During AP MLD link setup, a link ID is reserved before the link
is added to the MLD’s link list. If setup fails early
(e.g., due to a duplicate address), the cleanup path incorrectly
assumes the link was added and skips releasing the reserved ID,
leading to a leak. Repeated failures can eventually exhaust
the pool of available link IDs.

Fix this by releasing the reserved link ID when link setup fails
before adding it to the list. This prevents ID exhaustion
from repeated failures.

Fixes: Ib38233cbd(QSDK:HOSTAPD: WAR for crash during rmmod insmod test)

Signed-off-by: Yuvarani V <yuvarani@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/hostapd.c | 14 ++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/hostapd.c b/src/ap/hostapd.c
index 4626ddb..020b29b 100644
--- a/src/ap/hostapd.c
+++ b/src/ap/hostapd.c
@@ -6419,8 +6419,18 @@ int hostapd_mld_remove_link(struct hostapd_data *hapd)
 	if (!mld)
 		return -1;
 
-	if (hapd->link.next == NULL || hapd->link.prev == NULL)
-		return -1;
+	/*
+	 * If the link was never added to the MLD list (e.g., failure during
+	 * interface add), we still need to release the allocated link ID.
+	 * In that case, do not touch the link list or num_links, but ensure
+	 * the ID becomes available again.
+	 */
+	if (hapd->link.next == NULL || hapd->link.prev == NULL) {
+		mld->free_links |= BIT(hapd->mld_link_id);
+		wpa_printf(MSG_DEBUG, "AP MLD %s: Link ID %d released (not linked)",
+			   mld->name, hapd->mld_link_id);
+		return 0;
+	}
 
 	dl_list_del(&hapd->link);
 	mld->free_links |= BIT(hapd->mld_link_id);
-- 
